1
00:00:44,837 --> 00:00:46,589
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

2
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:55,848
There's no way he'll check online.

3
00:00:55,931 --> 00:00:56,807
Not him.

4
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,977
Like he'd ever look up We Were Friends.

5
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:01,562
Not him.

6
00:01:03,105 --> 00:01:04,523
There's absolutely no way.

7
00:01:09,695 --> 00:01:10,529
PAZER WEB NOVEL PORTAL

8
00:01:10,613 --> 00:01:12,031
WE WERE FRIENDS

9
00:01:12,114 --> 00:01:15,826
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

10
00:01:17,620 --> 00:01:19,038
…YOON ONLY HAD EYES FOR TAE-HA…

11
00:01:29,340 --> 00:01:31,509
Unbelievable. You little…

12
00:01:39,058 --> 00:01:40,309
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 1

13
00:01:44,230 --> 00:01:45,231
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 2

14
00:01:47,191 --> 00:01:48,275
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 3

15
00:01:50,361 --> 00:01:52,780
END OF EPISODE 3

16
00:02:01,288 --> 00:02:04,834
CHAPTER 23: YOUR ROUGH THOUGHTS
AND ANXIOUS LOOKS

17
00:02:09,964 --> 00:02:12,341
EPISODE 7

18
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:15,177
You know what?

19
00:02:15,261 --> 00:02:16,762
By the looks of things,

20
00:02:16,846 --> 00:02:18,472
EBC is also excited

21
00:02:18,973 --> 00:02:21,016
about the math class.

22
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:24,186
I don't blame them.

23
00:02:24,270 --> 00:02:26,689
After all, it is taught by a math genius.

24
00:02:27,356 --> 00:02:29,233
-Right?
-Sure.

25
00:02:30,234 --> 00:02:32,653
Of course,
I totally respect your decision.

26
00:02:32,736 --> 00:02:33,946
There's no pressure.

27
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:35,322
-No pressure at all.
-No.

28
00:02:35,406 --> 00:02:39,785
But sometimes,
people do change their minds.

29
00:02:39,869 --> 00:02:41,495
So, I thought I'd ask one last time.

30
00:02:41,579 --> 00:02:42,955
In case you've changed…

31
00:02:43,038 --> 00:02:44,039
I guess you haven't.

32
00:02:48,294 --> 00:02:49,837
Do something, will you?

33
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:00,764
Today's the day.

34
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:04,810
Until we're are done with filming,

35
00:03:04,894 --> 00:03:08,939
until EBC crew wraps up and leaves school,

36
00:03:09,023 --> 00:03:11,483
I want everyone to stay sharp

37
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:14,862
and refrain from saying anything
that could harm the school's reputation.

38
00:03:15,696 --> 00:03:16,947
Homeroom teachers,

39
00:03:17,031 --> 00:03:19,074
check your students' uniforms

40
00:03:19,158 --> 00:03:21,702
and make sure
they're on their best behavior.

41
00:03:21,785 --> 00:03:24,413
Hopefully, everything will go off
without a hitch.

42
00:03:24,997 --> 00:03:27,249
Let's make sure this is a success.

43
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,460
We got this!

44
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:30,711
-Okay.
-Of course.

45
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:33,297
Especially, our new teachers.

46
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,257
And the star of the show,

47
00:03:35,883 --> 00:03:37,259
Mr. Ga Woo-su.

48
00:03:38,052 --> 00:03:42,389
Mr. Ga Woo-su.

49
00:03:42,473 --> 00:03:44,266
-Yes.
-Thank you in advance.

50
00:03:45,351 --> 00:03:48,145
Let's get this done!

51
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:51,565
Da-ju, everything's sorted, right?

52
00:03:51,649 --> 00:03:54,985
Yes, by hook or by crook,
we'll get what we need.

53
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:58,280
Aunt Young-hee.

54
00:04:00,616 --> 00:04:02,660
Here's the man of the hour.

55
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:05,663
How is it that you look so good

56
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:08,791
in such flamboyant clothes?

57
00:04:08,874 --> 00:04:11,251
Then, I'll put my faith in you.

58
00:04:11,335 --> 00:04:12,795
-Yes, ma'am.
-Good.

59
00:04:14,713 --> 00:04:17,508
So, you're the principal's nephew.

60
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:28,018
Aunt Young-hee, clearly,
the highlight of today's filming

61
00:04:28,102 --> 00:04:29,645
will be my flute solo.

62
00:04:29,728 --> 00:04:32,648
When the curtains open
to reveal me on stage,

63
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:34,400
the spotlight will shine on me.

64
00:04:34,483 --> 00:04:36,944
Basically, it'll be game over then.

65
00:04:37,027 --> 00:04:38,946
Drink this.

66
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:43,701
What?

67
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:50,124
This is from my favorite place.

68
00:04:50,207 --> 00:04:51,959
I know.

69
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:54,128
Drink up.

70
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:55,963
Keep drinking.

71
00:04:57,381 --> 00:05:00,134
Go on, get every last drop.

72
00:05:25,451 --> 00:05:26,618
You play so well.

73
00:05:26,702 --> 00:05:29,830
I might have to quit teaching
when the episode airs.

74
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:36,712
Did you see the new guys
have all turned up in suits?

75
00:05:36,795 --> 00:05:37,921
Honestly.

76
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:41,884
At best, they'll be caught
in the background for a split second.

77
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:44,344
I actually feel sorry for them.

78
00:05:44,428 --> 00:05:46,221
Tell me about it.

79
00:05:47,473 --> 00:05:49,683
It's not kicking in right away.

80
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:50,893
Huh? What was that?

81
00:05:59,193 --> 00:06:02,237
There's no time for this.
I should go rehearse with the camera crew.

82
00:06:11,455 --> 00:06:15,501
I'm sorry about this, E-den.

83
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:17,753
Film him on the sly?

84
00:06:17,836 --> 00:06:18,962
Come on.

85
00:06:19,046 --> 00:06:21,715
Don't put it like that.
You make it sound illegal.

86
00:06:22,299 --> 00:06:26,136
If you just happen to turn this on,

87
00:06:27,846 --> 00:06:30,516
it will just happen to record
whatever's in front of it.

88
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,601
I can't.

89
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:33,852
I really can't.

90
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:37,022
I need to keep my head down.

91
00:06:37,106 --> 00:06:39,358
If I mess up again, I'll end up in jail.

92
00:06:40,818 --> 00:06:42,027
Wait, sit back down.

93
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:45,489
I know Woo-su is a bit of a tyrant,

94
00:06:45,572 --> 00:06:47,157
but he wouldn't send a student to jail.

95
00:06:47,699 --> 00:06:48,659
You have to do this

96
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:51,286
to make up for all the time
you goofed off in my class.

97
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:53,747
The gall of writing an essay in my class.

98
00:06:53,831 --> 00:06:55,499
Do you know how hurt I was?

99
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:59,753
I'm really sorry about that, but…

100
00:07:01,213 --> 00:07:03,757
There's a good reason
why I'm entrusting this to you.

101
00:07:03,841 --> 00:07:05,134
Don't you see that?

102
00:07:05,217 --> 00:07:06,468
No.

103
00:07:08,303 --> 00:07:09,388
If you don't do this,

104
00:07:11,515 --> 00:07:12,975
we'll all be fired.

105
00:07:13,058 --> 00:07:14,184
Are you okay with that?

106
00:07:14,268 --> 00:07:15,435
Fired?

107
00:07:16,603 --> 00:07:19,064
Principal's orders.

108
00:07:19,857 --> 00:07:21,400
You know how she'll react

109
00:07:21,483 --> 00:07:23,110
if we disobey her.

110
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:24,027
If we get fired,

111
00:07:24,945 --> 00:07:25,863
I'll be fine.

112
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:29,491
But…

113
00:07:30,492 --> 00:07:34,454
I'm not sure Mr. Jung and Mr. Yoon
will land on their feet so easily.

114
00:07:36,498 --> 00:07:38,542
Why not?

115
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:43,005
Mr. Jung will struggle to get another job
because of his leg.

116
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:47,217
And as for Mr. Yoon, well…

117
00:07:58,061 --> 00:07:59,354
That can't happen.

118
00:07:59,438 --> 00:08:00,397
Exactly.

119
00:08:00,981 --> 00:08:01,815
That can't happen.

120
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:03,525
And besides,

121
00:08:05,569 --> 00:08:06,820
I know everything.

122
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:08,614
About what?

123
00:08:09,114 --> 00:08:10,115
Seriously?

124
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:12,618
I'm more observant than you think.

125
00:08:13,327 --> 00:08:14,953
I could tell right away.

126
00:08:15,037 --> 00:08:16,705
Did you really think I wouldn't notice?

127
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:21,293
I'm not sure what you're talking about.

128
00:08:23,712 --> 00:08:25,339
I knew all along.

129
00:08:26,465 --> 00:08:27,591
Right from the beginning.

130
00:08:29,551 --> 00:08:31,428
Your rough thoughts

131
00:08:32,179 --> 00:08:33,347
and anxious looks.

132
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:35,599
How could I not know?

133
00:08:37,935 --> 00:08:39,144
I'll keep it a secret

134
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:40,938
as long as you film.

135
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:42,022
Okay?

136
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:50,572
How does he know about my novel?

137
00:08:53,242 --> 00:08:55,327
Come on, kids.
This isn't the time for idle chats.

138
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:57,079
Don't you know
the camera crew is here today?

139
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,080
You girls should…

140
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:03,293
Don't forget
you're the face of our school!

141
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:07,839
Kids, why aren't any of you studying?

142
00:09:09,424 --> 00:09:11,760
Chat away in English.

143
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:14,012
Solve some math problems too.
They're a delight, no?

144
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:15,764
Hey.

145
00:09:16,974 --> 00:09:17,808
Hello?

146
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:20,602
Hey, kid.

147
00:09:20,686 --> 00:09:21,853
Ji-a.

148
00:09:22,437 --> 00:09:23,563
Ji-a.

149
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:28,610
Where's your uniform?

150
00:09:30,279 --> 00:09:31,321
I washed it.

151
00:09:31,405 --> 00:09:32,322
Why?

152
00:09:33,031 --> 00:09:36,535
Why wash it
when you have to wear it to school?

153
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:38,787
I got oil on it.

154
00:09:40,998 --> 00:09:43,709
You should have still worn it
even if it had oil stains.

155
00:09:43,792 --> 00:09:47,587
You should have worn it even if it was
still soaking wet from the laundry.

156
00:09:47,671 --> 00:09:49,673
Why today of all days?

157
00:09:49,756 --> 00:09:50,757
Where's your gym clothes?

158
00:09:50,841 --> 00:09:51,842
I don't have them with me.

159
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:54,136
Then borrow one and get changed.

160
00:09:54,761 --> 00:09:55,929
Never mind.

161
00:09:56,013 --> 00:09:57,931
That's not necessary. What's your name?

162
00:09:58,015 --> 00:09:59,099
Choi Ji-a, ma'am.

163
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:00,600
Bring your desk and come with me.

164
00:10:01,476 --> 00:10:02,894
Come on, don't dawdle.

165
00:10:02,978 --> 00:10:04,521
There's no time.

166
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:08,150
What's going on?

167
00:10:09,818 --> 00:10:11,403
Mr. Ga.

168
00:10:12,321 --> 00:10:14,489
I'm going to take Choi Ji-a

169
00:10:14,573 --> 00:10:17,326
and have her study in the counseling room
until the fifth period.

170
00:10:17,909 --> 00:10:20,078
-Bring your desk this way.
-Go back to the classroom.

171
00:10:22,164 --> 00:10:23,415
Mr. Ga.

172
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:25,959
Can I have a word?

173
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:32,674
As you know,
we have the EBC crew here filming today.

174
00:10:32,758 --> 00:10:34,926
She sleeps through class anyway,

175
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:37,095
and she isn't even wearing her uniform.

176
00:10:37,179 --> 00:10:40,474
What's more,
look at the state of her clothes.

177
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:43,310
Today is such an important day.

178
00:10:43,393 --> 00:10:44,978
Given she might ruin
the school's reputation,

179
00:10:45,062 --> 00:10:46,521
it's better she's not here at all.

180
00:10:46,605 --> 00:10:49,858
I'm terrified she'll end up on camera.

181
00:10:50,901 --> 00:10:53,570
I still don't think it calls for
hiding one of our students.

182
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:57,949
Don't be so naive, Mr. Ga.

183
00:10:58,033 --> 00:11:00,327
TV shows are all scripted anyway.

184
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:02,037
Just until fifth period, okay?

185
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,246
Hey.

186
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:05,415
If you won't allow Ji-a
to be here for the shoot,

187
00:11:06,041 --> 00:11:09,294
then none of my class
will take part in it.

188
00:11:14,591 --> 00:11:15,884
Says who?

189
00:11:16,802 --> 00:11:17,886
Mr. Ga.

190
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:20,680
I believe I made myself clear.

191
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:23,016
Let's go.

192
00:11:23,809 --> 00:11:24,810
Pick it up.

193
00:11:39,741 --> 00:11:40,617
Darn it.

194
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,247
I'll deal with you later, Mr. Ga.

195
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:46,498
Are they here?

196
00:11:47,249 --> 00:11:48,291
I'm coming.

197
00:11:50,544 --> 00:11:52,295
Go back inside.
Everyone back to your seats.

198
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:04,933
CHAPTER 24:
OUR SCHOOL RIGHT NOW

199
00:12:27,873 --> 00:12:30,750
Why did you choose Murim Girls' High?

200
00:12:39,009 --> 00:12:39,843
Our school…

201
00:12:39,926 --> 00:12:42,762
I'm Kim Dan-ji,
the Murim Girls' High connection.

202
00:12:42,846 --> 00:12:46,016
The sports field is really nice.
What else?

203
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:49,478
And we've got a really hot teacher.

204
00:12:49,561 --> 00:12:51,104
-That's Mr. Yoon Dong-ju.
-For real. No!

205
00:12:51,188 --> 00:12:52,606
-No, Mr. Jung Gi-jeon--
-Mr. Yoon.

206
00:12:52,689 --> 00:12:55,442
-Come on, Mr. Noh's the hot one.
-No, that's Mr. Jung.

207
00:12:57,027 --> 00:12:59,988
I don't think I can do it. Really.

208
00:13:00,614 --> 00:13:01,573
Yes, you can!

209
00:13:02,157 --> 00:13:04,326
There's nothing you can't do.

210
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:06,036
Don't be so negative.

211
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:08,747
Remember, all Murim students
are full of potential.

212
00:13:08,830 --> 00:13:10,040
-Go for it.
-How is that relevant?

213
00:13:10,123 --> 00:13:11,458
He's here.

214
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:12,584
I'm off. Don't mess up.

215
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:13,502
Got it?

216
00:13:24,596 --> 00:13:26,932
Don't overthink this problem.

217
00:13:27,015 --> 00:13:29,935
There are two solutions
with the given conditions.

218
00:13:30,018 --> 00:13:31,937
First, the value of x…

219
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:34,523
If he catches me filming him,
he'll go ballistic.

220
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:36,566
And the tangent line…

221
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:40,529
On the other hand,
he has told them about my novel

222
00:13:40,612 --> 00:13:42,364
after telling me he'd keep it a secret.

223
00:13:42,447 --> 00:13:43,532
Let's just do it.

224
00:13:43,615 --> 00:13:44,741
Mr. Ga.

225
00:13:47,244 --> 00:13:48,078
I…

226
00:13:48,787 --> 00:13:50,455
have a question.

227
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:54,084
What is it?

228
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:01,091
Well, I heard

229
00:14:01,716 --> 00:14:04,469
a famous university in another country

230
00:14:04,553 --> 00:14:07,055
offered you a job as a professor.

231
00:14:07,138 --> 00:14:09,099
Why did you come here instead?

232
00:14:12,269 --> 00:14:13,520
Why are you asking that now?

233
00:14:15,981 --> 00:14:18,149
I've been curious all along.

234
00:14:18,775 --> 00:14:22,612
It's amazing to have a genius like you
teaching at our school.

235
00:14:23,238 --> 00:14:26,533
I thought there might be a special reason.

236
00:14:30,662 --> 00:14:33,290
Isn't a question like that
better saved for after class?

237
00:14:34,165 --> 00:14:37,794
Mr. Ga, we're all curious.

238
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:40,922
-Tell us.
-If you tell us, we'll study harder.

239
00:14:41,006 --> 00:14:42,465
-Tell us!
-Tell us!

240
00:14:42,549 --> 00:14:43,717
-Tell us!
-Tell us!

241
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,970
-Tell us!
-Tell us!

242
00:14:47,053 --> 00:14:48,138
-Tell us!
-Quiet, everyone.

243
00:14:50,056 --> 00:14:51,182
Fine.

244
00:14:51,266 --> 00:14:54,603
I guess it might be helpful
in thinking about your own futures.

245
00:14:58,815 --> 00:15:01,735
The six kids invited
to the Mathematical Olympiad

246
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:03,820
attend two separate training camps.

247
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:05,572
On the day of the first camp,

248
00:15:05,655 --> 00:15:09,326
as soon as we finished registering,
our first exam was waiting for us.

249
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:10,785
That exam…

250
00:15:48,156 --> 00:15:48,990
Take it out.

251
00:15:51,451 --> 00:15:52,369
I said take it out.

252
00:16:11,888 --> 00:16:15,433
Mr. Ga! Just a moment. Let me explain.

253
00:16:15,517 --> 00:16:18,144
Mr. Noh told me if I didn't do it,

254
00:16:18,228 --> 00:16:19,771
you'd all get fired.

255
00:16:19,854 --> 00:16:22,190
That's the only reason I did it, sir.

256
00:16:22,273 --> 00:16:23,525
Please hear me out, sir.

257
00:16:23,608 --> 00:16:26,027
We can't have you all lose your jobs,
can we, sir?

258
00:16:27,278 --> 00:16:28,113
Noh Da-ju.

259
00:16:28,196 --> 00:16:30,073
You asked a student
to film me behind my back?

260
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:31,074
Have you lost it?

261
00:16:35,203 --> 00:16:37,580
Mr. Ga, why don't you calm down

262
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:39,207
so we can talk about it?

263
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:41,960
What do you mean
by filming behind your back?

264
00:16:42,043 --> 00:16:43,044
Who would…

265
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,588
do something so unethical?

266
00:16:46,673 --> 00:16:48,425
How could you film me like this?

267
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:49,884
You of all people should know better.

268
00:16:49,968 --> 00:16:50,885
Guys.

269
00:16:50,969 --> 00:16:52,220
What's going on?

270
00:16:52,303 --> 00:16:53,388
Hey.

271
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:55,140
That was so long ago.

272
00:16:55,223 --> 00:16:56,808
You have to move on.

273
00:16:56,891 --> 00:16:58,017
You can't go on like this.

274
00:17:01,521 --> 00:17:03,773
Hey!

275
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:06,860
Mr. Ga.

276
00:17:10,864 --> 00:17:12,282
May I have a word?

277
00:17:28,757 --> 00:17:29,591
Sir.

278
00:17:29,674 --> 00:17:32,677
-Jeez, you idiot.
-What's the matter?

279
00:17:32,761 --> 00:17:35,346
Did something happen
to Mr. Ga in the past?

280
00:17:41,436 --> 00:17:43,021
I don't know the details.

281
00:17:44,147 --> 00:17:45,565
But when Woo-su was about ten,

282
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:49,694
someone started stalking him
after he was on TV as a math prodigy.

283
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:51,988
I heard that crazy stalker

284
00:17:52,655 --> 00:17:54,783
would turn up at his school and his house

285
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:58,119
to film and take photos of him
behind his back.

286
00:17:58,787 --> 00:17:59,829
Eventually,

287
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:02,582
he even kidnapped him.

288
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:05,293
Kidnapped?

289
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:16,513
That left Woo-su traumatized.

290
00:18:27,816 --> 00:18:29,317
My goodness.

291
00:18:30,735 --> 00:18:32,028
What's wrong?

292
00:18:33,488 --> 00:18:34,906
Mr. Ga.

293
00:18:34,989 --> 00:18:37,116
This is the real world.

294
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,743
You might be smart,

295
00:18:38,827 --> 00:18:40,995
but being obedient

296
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:43,623
will help you get further in life.

297
00:18:43,706 --> 00:18:45,917
It won't kill you to get filmed,

298
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,294
so what's the big deal?

299
00:18:52,382 --> 00:18:53,341
Please excuse me.

300
00:18:54,551 --> 00:18:56,678
If you're not going to cooperate,

301
00:18:56,761 --> 00:18:58,763
you leave me no choice.

302
00:19:06,771 --> 00:19:08,398
SUSPENSION NOTICE

303
00:19:09,065 --> 00:19:10,608
YOON DONG-JU

304
00:19:10,692 --> 00:19:13,653
The rest of you might land on your feet,

305
00:19:14,529 --> 00:19:18,324
but if Mr. Yoon loses his job here,
he'll struggle.

306
00:19:26,541 --> 00:19:27,375
From this equation,

307
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:30,420
it's clear that negative four is
the average rate of change.

308
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:32,672
Next, we have to calculate f prime of x.

309
00:19:34,257 --> 00:19:35,633
Two x minus three.

310
00:19:35,717 --> 00:19:37,635
What was the average rate of change again?

311
00:19:37,719 --> 00:19:39,345
-Negative four.
-Negative four.

312
00:19:40,722 --> 00:19:42,140
It was negative four.

313
00:19:46,769 --> 00:19:49,981
He could have just filmed from the start.
Why all the drama?

314
00:19:51,107 --> 00:19:52,317
Tell me about it.

315
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,611
We're going to end up finishing late
because of him.

316
00:19:54,694 --> 00:19:56,112
-I'm so annoyed.
-So the value of x

317
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:57,322
is negative one-half,

318
00:19:57,405 --> 00:20:00,950
which happens to be a number
between negative three and two.

319
00:20:04,495 --> 00:20:06,205
Accordingly, c is…

320
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:12,921
It's finally over.

321
00:20:13,004 --> 00:20:15,173
CHAPTER 25: I ONLY FEEL BETRAYED
BECAUSE I TRUSTED YOU

322
00:20:29,103 --> 00:20:29,938
Aunt Young-hee.

323
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:32,440
Wait, what am I doing here?

324
00:20:33,024 --> 00:20:36,152
You said you were going to take a nap
because you didn't sleep well last night,

325
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,196
and you've been asleep all this time.

326
00:20:39,614 --> 00:20:40,448
Did I?

327
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:42,408
That doesn't make sense.

328
00:20:43,117 --> 00:20:44,160
What about the filming?

329
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:46,579
It's all over.

330
00:20:46,663 --> 00:20:47,580
What?

331
00:20:48,206 --> 00:20:49,624
No way.

332
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:51,793
No.

333
00:20:53,461 --> 00:20:54,295
No.

334
00:20:54,379 --> 00:20:56,130
No. Don't go. Stop.

335
00:20:56,214 --> 00:20:58,549
I can't believe this!

336
00:20:58,633 --> 00:21:00,218
Don't go!

337
00:21:00,301 --> 00:21:03,137
No!

338
00:21:34,377 --> 00:21:36,462
You're not a snake charmer!

339
00:21:53,938 --> 00:21:55,148
Sir…

340
00:21:59,694 --> 00:22:00,778
Mr. Ga.

341
00:22:27,388 --> 00:22:28,890
I…

342
00:22:29,599 --> 00:22:30,600
Mr. Ga.

343
00:22:33,311 --> 00:22:35,021
I'm so sorry.

344
00:22:36,189 --> 00:22:39,817
I would never have filmed you
if I had known what had happened to you.

345
00:22:41,152 --> 00:22:42,111
No.

346
00:22:42,195 --> 00:22:44,113
I shouldn't have filmed you regardless.

347
00:22:44,197 --> 00:22:46,449
I'm really sorry. I made a mistake.

348
00:22:54,248 --> 00:22:56,084
You asked me a question in math class.

349
00:22:57,335 --> 00:22:59,796
Do you know what flashed through my head
at that exact moment?

350
00:23:03,633 --> 00:23:05,301
"Is she actually
starting to like math now?"

351
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:13,559
When I heard your question,
I went, "All right."

352
00:23:14,811 --> 00:23:16,312
"It's a tangent, but it's a start."

353
00:23:17,688 --> 00:23:19,232
I figured my story

354
00:23:19,315 --> 00:23:21,818
might get you interested in math,

355
00:23:22,693 --> 00:23:24,612
so I was going to
give you a sincere answer.

356
00:23:27,281 --> 00:23:28,199
But you…

357
00:23:34,956 --> 00:23:36,124
I guess I only feel betrayed

358
00:23:36,707 --> 00:23:38,501
because I trusted you.

359
00:23:40,545 --> 00:23:41,879
Forget it. Just go.

360
00:23:47,385 --> 00:23:49,178
I apologize for

361
00:23:49,804 --> 00:23:50,972
disappointing you.

362
00:23:52,265 --> 00:23:53,099
Just go.

363
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:11,909
Get up.

364
00:24:13,077 --> 00:24:14,704
I said get up. Enough with the acting.

365
00:24:22,086 --> 00:24:23,171
Eui-ju.

366
00:24:25,089 --> 00:24:26,048
Eui-ju.

367
00:24:28,050 --> 00:24:30,052
Hey, Eui-ju.

368
00:24:30,136 --> 00:24:31,512
Wake up, Eui-ju!

369
00:24:32,763 --> 00:24:34,098
Eui-ju.

370
00:24:34,182 --> 00:24:35,349
Stay with me, Eui-ju!

371
00:25:51,550 --> 00:25:53,552
Subtitle: Paul Carver
